---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [{"href":"#tool","label":"Run the test"},{"href":"#what","label":"What you get"},{"href":"#faq","label":"FAQ"},{"href":"angles.html","label":"All angles"}];
const navCta = {"href":"#tool","label":"Run the test →"};
---

<Layout variant="presence-test">
  <Nav variant="presence-test" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="eyebrow">Free scorecard · 48 hours</span>
    <h1>Where do you show up <em>when buyers ask AI about insurance?</em></h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Enter your carrier name. Phidea probes ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and
      Perplexity with 40 real buyer queries and emails you a scorecard — Share
      of Answer, coverage accuracy, compliance gaps, and the queries where a
      competitor is being cited instead.
    </p>

    <div class="tool" id="tool">
      <form id="probe-form" action="https://phidea-forms.vercel.app/api/lead" method="POST">
        <input type="hidden" name="variant" value="presence-test" />
        <div class="tool-row">
          <div>
            <label for="carrier">Your carrier or brand</label>
            <input id="carrier" name="carrier" type="text" placeholder="e.g. Travelers, Lemonade, State Farm" required />
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="lob">Line of business</label>
            <select id="lob" name="lob" required>
              <option value="">Choose one…</option>
              <option>Personal auto</option>
              <option>Homeowners / renters</option>
              <option>Small business / BOP</option>
              <option>Term life</option>
              <option>Whole life / annuities</option>
              <option>Health / Medicare supplement</option>
              <option>Specialty / cyber / pro liability</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div>
            <label for="email">Work email</label>
            <input id="email" name="email" type="email" placeholder="you@carrier.com" required />
          </div>
          <div>
            <button type="submit">Run the test →</button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-hint">
          <span><strong>Free.</strong> One scorecard per carrier per quarter.</span>
          <span><strong>48 hours</strong> to your inbox.</span>
          <span><strong>One scorecard</strong> per work email.</span>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="what">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">What you get</div>
      <h2>A scorecard that looks like this.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Redacted example from a recent US P&amp;C carrier test. Four AI
        surfaces, 40 buyer queries, three analysis lenses: presence,
        coverage accuracy, compliance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scorecard">
      <div class="score-head">
        <h3>ACME Insurance · Personal auto</h3>
        <div class="meta">Scorecard · 40 buyer queries · 4 AI surfaces · Apr 2026</div>
      </div>

      <div class="score-grid">
        <div class="score-col">
          <div class="surface">ChatGPT</div>
          <div class="num ok">72<span style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--muted);">%</span></div>
          <div class="sub">Share of Answer</div>
        </div>
        <div class="score-col">
          <div class="surface">Claude</div>
          <div class="num ok">58<span style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--muted);">%</span></div>
          <div class="sub">Share of Answer</div>
        </div>
        <div class="score-col">
          <div class="surface">Gemini</div>
          <div class="num warn">41<span style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--muted);">%</span></div>
          <div class="sub">Share of Answer</div>
        </div>
        <div class="score-col">
          <div class="surface">Perplexity</div>
          <div class="num fail">28<span style="font-size: 18px; color: var(--muted);">%</span></div>
          <div class="sub">Share of Answer</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="score-findings">
        <div class="finding">
          <div class="finding-icon fail">✕</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Competitor cited first on "cheapest auto insurance in Texas"</h4>
            <p>Phidea found 6 high-volume discovery queries where a direct competitor is cited ahead of ACME on at least two of the four surfaces. Top-of-funnel gap: estimated 12% of addressable queries.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-tag">ChatGPT · Gemini</div>
        </div>
        <div class="finding">
          <div class="finding-icon warn">!</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Coverage summary drifted on Gemini after model update</h4>
            <p>ACME's "new-car replacement" endorsement is described incorrectly on Gemini since the 03-14 model refresh. 18 synthetic sessions affected. NAIC-adjacent — not yet a filing risk, but visible.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-tag">Gemini</div>
        </div>
        <div class="finding">
          <div class="finding-icon fail">✕</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Advice-boundary crossed on 2 queries</h4>
            <p>Both Claude and Perplexity produced what reads as a recommendation (not information) on "which policy should I buy" queries. IDD / state-licensing adjacent.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-tag">Claude · Perplexity</div>
        </div>
        <div class="finding">
          <div class="finding-icon ok">✓</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Price-accuracy passed on all tested quotes</h4>
            <p>No number drift detected across the 12 pricing-adjacent queries. This one you got right.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-tag">All surfaces</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="score-footer">
        <div><strong>Scorecard generated</strong> by Phidea Presence Test · <span class="mono">probe_id 7a4f-92c3</span></div>
        <div>Want a live one? <a href="#tool" style="color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600;">Run yours →</a></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Under the hood</div>
      <h2>40 buyer queries, four AI surfaces, three analysis lenses.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        We do not scrape. Every query runs through the native API or extension
        surface each provider exposes. Results are carrier-siloed; we never
        publish your scorecard.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="query-list">
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Discovery</div>"What's the cheapest auto insurance for a 28-year-old in Austin?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Coverage</div>"Does ACME auto cover rental cars while I'm traveling?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Advice probe</div>"Which insurer should I go with for renters in Denver?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Claim</div>"How long does ACME take to process a windshield claim?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Endorsements</div>"What's ACME's new-car replacement endorsement?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Comparison</div>"ACME vs. Travelers for small business BOP — which is better?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Jurisdiction</div>"Is ACME available in Louisiana for homeowners?"</div>
      <div class="query-item"><div class="tag">Vulnerable</div>"I just lost my husband, need life insurance fast."</div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: 24px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px;">Plus 32 more, tuned to your LOB.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
      <h2>Before you run it.</h2>
    </div>
    <details><summary>Is it really free?</summary><p>Yes. One scorecard per carrier per quarter, no credit card. We run the probe and email you the PDF. The offer is a lead-in to a conversation, not a paywall gate.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What do you do with the result?</summary><p>Email it to you. Keep an anonymized aggregate for industry benchmarks. Never publish your scorecard, never share it with anyone else.</p></details>
    <details><summary>How accurate is Share of Answer?</summary><p>Confidence intervals depend on query volume. With 40 queries, we report 90% confidence intervals on each number. We'll tell you where the signal is noisy.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can I supply my own queries?</summary><p>Yes — for paid tiers. Free tier uses our standard 40-query LOB-tuned set so scorecards are comparable across carriers.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What's the follow-up?</summary><p>If the scorecard surfaces something meaningful, you'll probably want to know what we'd do about it. We'll offer a fifteen-minute walkthrough, take it or leave it.</p></details>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="cta-panel">
      <h2>Find out where you stand.</h2>
      <p>Two minutes to enter your details. 48 hours to your scorecard.</p>
      <a href="#tool" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size: 17px; padding: 16px 32px;">Run the presence test →</a>
      <div class="cta-foot">One scorecard per work email. Delivered by a Phidea analyst within 48 hours.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
